      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 39
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is a mechanically sorted driver\u2019s car powered by the 3.6L M96 flat-six featuring VarioCam Plus. The high-revving boxer engine delivers power through a G96 6-speed manual transaxle with precise gate entry and no synchro hesitation. This example has been proactively maintained with a ceramic IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh Rear Main Seal (RMS), mitigating common M96 failure points. The suspension retains its factory-intended geometry, utilizing a multi-link rear setup that provides exceptional mechanical grip and communicative steering feedback. While the Arctic Silver finish shows minor signs of spirited use, the underpinnings are robust, with no signs of bore scoring or oil aeration. A technically sound specimen for the purist seeking an authentic 911 experience.",
